Sentencas: This work is devoted to the mathematical modeling and experimental studies of electric-current generation during hydrogen oxidation in microtubular (MT) solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Mathematical Modeling and Experimental Studies of Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The technology of manufacturing fuel cells and the experimental technique are described.
Titulo: Mathematical Modeling and Experimental Studies of Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: A mathematical model is constructed that describes the occurrence of chemical reactions and diffusion and heat-transfer processes.
Titulo: Mathematical Modeling and Experimental Studies of Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: When verifying the model using the example of hydrogen oxidation in a temperature range of 600-850 degrees C, kinetic parameters are determined that make it possible to achieve the best agreement between experimental and model data.
Titulo: Mathematical Modeling and Experimental Studies of Microtubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
